balanceOf(address,uint256).details: Returns the value of tokens of token type `id` owned by `account`.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

params.tokenId: The ID of the RWA token

returns._0: AssetMetadata struct containing all asset information

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns true if `operator` is approved to transfer ``account``'s tokens. See {setApprovalForAll}.

params.lockupWeeks: Lockup period in weeks (0 for no lockup)
params.priceId: Pyth price feed ID for asset valuation
params.totalValue: Total value of the asset in USD cents

returns.tokenId: The ID of the newly minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.tokenId: The ID of the RWA token

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Grants or revokes permission to `operator` to transfer the caller's tokens, according to `approved`, Emits an {ApprovalForAll} event. Requirements: - `operator` cannot be the zero address.

params.newuri: New base URI for token metadata

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the ERC]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.

burn(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Burn fractions (implements IRWATokenFactory interface for FractionManager)

getAssetMetadata(uint256).notice: Get metadata for a specific RWA token

mint(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Mint whole token (implements IRWATokenFactory interface for FractionManager)

mintRWAToken(string,uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Mint new RWA tokens with issuer-defined fraction specs

purchaseFraction(uint256,uint256,bytes).notice: Purchase fractions of an RWA token

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.notice: Override safeBatchTransferFrom to integrate FractionManager validation

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Override safeTransferFrom to integrate FractionManager validation

setURI(string).notice: Update the URI for token metadata
